    "Edmond later wrote enthusiastically of Constable and Turner.": [],
    "They were not visionaries of the art of their own era and were relatively unimpressed with and sometimes critical of the Impressionists, except for Edmond's praise of Degas' originality.": [],
    "Their chief modern artist was the (now largely forgotten) artist Paul Gavarni (Sulpice Guillaume Chevalier, 1804-1866).": [
