    "After Edmond's death, the brothers' importance waned until the second half of the 20th century when they were recognized as the leaders of much of modernism in French art writing and taste.": [],
    "The Goncourt <em>Journal</em> is an important primary source for Parisian literary and artistic life.": [],
    "The Goncourts' ability to combine their knowledge of artistic life with compelling journalism (and publicity) resulted in their considerable influence on French taste in the second half of the 19th century.": [
        [
            4,
            13,
            [
                "Goncourt"
            ]
