    "They \"absorbed the Romanticism of the thirties and abandoned themselves feverishly to the realism, the meticulous modernism, of the fifties\" (Ironsides).": [],
    "They early on sensed the lifeless academic nature of much of the work of Raphael, who was at the time perhaps the most valued artist of the nineteenth century.": [],
    "A major theme of the Goncourts was that of artistic technique, which they often referred to as 'cuisine.\"": [
